blogpost:
This event was rather spontaneous. I pitched the idea on twitter on Monday, had three volunteers in seven minutes, and now we're uploading it five days later. Time flies, man. I'm quite fond of this event; it's just a global version of Party Games, sure, but it guarantees that everyone is thrown out of their comfort zone; you never know what to expect, and being good at PvP won't save you if the number falls on Turbo Kart Racers. Granted, I'm probably mostly fond of it because it allows casuals like me to compete, but still; it was the most fun I've had recording in a long time, and I recommend other people try it. (If your video goes viral and gets 10,000,000 views I'll be slightly butt-hurt but at that point you'd have too many views to care anyways)

Stayed up all night editing this because the video deserved it. Certainly not Disney levels of production, but I was learning as I went along. People tend to joke about me not editing, but the truth is, most videos don't need editing, nor do they benefit from too much of it. This was different, though. This was a video that could actually benefit from editing, so I tried my best. Apologies for sound problems, since this was recorded on my new PC the option to record my microphone into a separate sound track had been disabled, essentially making it 5x harder to do sound balancing. I think it turned out alright, though. I hope you enjoy this video, since it was easily my favorite video to make in a LONG time (possibly ever, but that might be the sleep deprivation talking). I used subtitles when necessary to emphasize lines in particularly chaotic situations; hopefully makes it easier to understand what people said while also showing just how chaotic it was. Some scenes will probably have to be watched twice to absorb all the dialogue, but i'm told rewatchability is a good thing. should probably have made a lot of subtitles smaller but too late now, rip. learning experience anyhow

The park was established on 18 May 1914 as the Salinas Forest Reserve covering the Salinas Salt Springs and surrounding forest through Executive Order No. 44 signed by Governor-General Francis Burton Harrison. In 1926, through amendments made in Proclamation No. 53 by Governor-General Leonard Wood, the forest reserve was re-established as the Salinas Deer Refuge. Salinas was finally declared a natural monument in 2000 under the National Integrated Protected Areas System through Proclamation No. 275 by President Joseph Estrada.

snippet.title: "Blitz" - Parody of "Blank Space" (has swearing)
snippet.description:
1200000000 likes and i'll make another song

because hot damn these things take a lot of work ;-;

This song is a parody of Blank Space by Taylor Swift. The song covers my timeline as a blitz player, from being a brand new player, to being the primary Blitz member of the Elite Team, and to the present, covering like, 15% of the issues Blitz has experienced over this time. Seriously, the song felt like it was way too long to record and way too short to write in enough about Blitz. fml

so follow me on twitter or something idk i want to be popular https://twitter.com/Technothepig

picture made like a year ago when I had 300 subs by the amazing Evvz:
https://www.youtube.com/user/TheRealE...

background music from this video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PEDZi...

lyrics:
getting bored
of Walls 2
I should find a new minigame
October, 2013
saw the game and I thought
oh my god
the fuck is this
so many 
op kits
but I guess
I’ll play a gaaaaaame
Horse tamers, every game
dominating winter all day long
everybody's kits the same
because it is so damn strong
but hey, I can survive
I get better ping here, than to the Hive
teams and hackers, everywhere
but nobody plays blitz to be fair

So I’ll keep on playing
and get horsetamer 6
My horse is fast but stupid
and I will call it Brick
Toxicologist gets added
with a level 5 stone sword
Keep going with a single dream that
one day I’ll be leaderboards

Gonna join another map...
but I know it’s all in vain
Trying to earn some coins..
but it’s not worth the pain
Got a long list of level 7s...
no high level kits I've gained...
keep getting rogue’d in deathmatch...
but that's just the game

Hypixel
gets a new host
I will miss you 30 ping
now it’s on
the east coast
but now I only want one thing
to get, the youtube rank
what the fuck it’s 30k subs
and I join the Elite teaaaaam
screaming, crying, horse users
as we nerf their kit to bits
don’t worry- toxic’s next
we’ll completely revamp blitz
make it
a whole new game
while i try, and rise to fame
I’ll make for, myself a name
when I’m done here this game will never be the same

so I release my first montage
become a rising star
people blame my hit detection
because of my 5 bar…
but it was the first of many,
and I buy armorer 10
people blame thorns constantly but
I still make one again

I name it Unexpected
later I release Life
my personal favorite
flawlesses left and right
but Blitz has some new problems
and this one’s pretty dumb
only one map ever fills up
… why is it Caelum?

remove caelum and replace it with v2
but it’s still half the things people queue
so many teams the forums explode
so we release an update: team mode

That was my last move,
and I leave the Elite Team
people ask me why but
I must follow my dreams
so I guess that marks the end of
my whole 9 month regime
but I’m telling you the game is
better off than it seems

So that was Blitz
it’s been over a year
nowadays there’s nothing
but lots of diamond gear
There’s five scouts in each round
it’s getting quite insane
I keep getting janitored but
that’s just the game

snippet.title: The Power of a Balanced Breakfast - Survival Games Montage
snippet.description:
I came here to eat cereal and kick ass. And I'm all out of frosted flakes. 

This wasn't supposed to be one montage- it was supposed to be four. It didn't start out as four, originally, I just wanted to create a masterpiece- one where players with upwards of 4000 wins were repeatedly smacked around for 3 minutes. But I also killed a lot of teams along the way, and I didn't want those clips to go to waste either, so I decided to make a teaming montage. And then I wanted a secondary, hype montage where all the poor 3000 win dudes could chill. And a montage for bowshots.

then i got fucking bored

so I decided to try out a new montage style, and see how people liked it. This style features all the highlights I could think of- leaderboard players, extremely high level players, teams (some of randoms, other of more high level players :3), and a few bow shots.

fun errors:
i ran out of planned footage like 6 minutes in and randomly tossed in some flawlesses because i was desperate leave me alone ;-;

In the last clip I get 3 arrow shots but the second one is hard to hear due to windows live having... slow sound adjustment changes. When I went to change it one file decided to stop working, which meant either spending an hour fine tuning it to what it had been previously, rendering, and then uploading... or saying fuck it. :P 

random fps drops for no apparent reason other than windows moviemaker being the fanciest editing program I feel like learning

Common salt is a mineral composed primarily of sodium chloride (NaCl), a chemical compound belonging to the larger class of salts; salt in its natural form as a crystalline mineral is known as rock salt or halite. Salt is present in vast quantities in the seawater, where it is the main mineral constituent; the open ocean has about 35 grams (1.2 oz) of solids per litre, a salinity of 3.5%. Salt is essential for animal life, and saltiness is one of the basic human tastes. The tissues of animals contain larger quantities of salt than do plant tissues; therefore the typical diets of nomads who subsist on their flocks and herds require little or no added salt, whereas cereal-based diets require supplementation. Salt is one of the oldest and most ubiquitous of food seasonings, and salting is an important method of food preservation.

Some of the earliest evidence of salt processing dates to around 8,000 years ago, when people living in Romania were boiling spring water to extract the salts; a saltworks in China has been found which dates to approximately the same period. Salt was prized by the ancient Hebrews, the Greeks, the Romans, the Byzantines, the Hittites and the Egyptians. Salt became an important article of trade and was transported by boat across the Mediterranean Sea, along specially built salt roads, and across the Sahara in camel caravans. The scarcity and universal need for salt has led nations to go to war over salt and use it to raise tax revenues. Salt is also used in religious ceremonies and has other cultural significance.

Salt is produced from salt mines or for the sea salt by the evaporation of seawater or mineral-rich spring water in shallow pools. Its major industrial products are caustic soda and chlorine, and it is used in many industrial processes and in the manufacture of polyvinyl chloride, plastics, paper pulp and many other products. Of the annual production of around two hundred million tonnes of salt, only about 6% is used for human consumption; other uses include water conditioning processes, de-icing highways and agricultural use. Edible salt is sold in forms such as sea salt and table salt which usually contains an anti-caking agent and may be iodised to prevent iodine deficiency. As well as its use in cooking and at the table, salt is present in many processed foods. Too much sodium in the diet raises blood pressure and may increase the risk of heart attacks and strokes. The World Health Organization recommends that adults should consume less than 2,000 mg of sodium which is equivalent to 5 grams of salt per day.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salt

The Colonization of Africa

Between the 1870s and 1900, Africa faced European imperialist aggression, diplomatic pressures, military invasions, and eventual conquest and colonization. At the same time, African societies put up various forms of resistance against the attempt to colonize their countries and impose foreign domination. By the early twentieth century, however, much of Africa, except Ethiopia and Liberia, had been colonized by European powers.
The European imperialist push into Africa was motivated by three main factors, economic, political, and social. It developed in the nineteenth century following the collapse of the profitability of the slave trade, its abolition and suppression, as well as the expansion of the European capitalist Industrial Revolution. The imperatives of capitalist industrialization—including the demand for assured sources of raw materials, the search for guaranteed markets and profitable investment outlets—spurred the European scramble and the partition and eventual conquest of Africa. Thus the primary motivation for European intrusion was economic.

Turns out people are starting to make montages almost as good as my other ones. So I had to turn up the heat. 3452 win average, LETS GO! But that's not enough. I had to do it... without high level kits.

I've heard two things that have highly annoyed me in my BSG Career: "You only win because of your OP kits!" and "Dumb MVPs and their p2w!"

So I decided to see how hard it would be to play without high level kits. But that wasn't enough. I ONLY played games with people who had extremely high level kits... my proof is this montage. Overall, my win ratio was a 40.45% and my kill/death ratio was 6.42, fighting high stats players with Scout 2.

And yes, I could have upgraded to Scout 7 easily... I certainly had the coins. But I kept my scout at level 2... because it proved a point. 

This was quite an adventure, and it helped me learn a lot about how blitz was for the ordinary player- I will use these experiences to help me balance the game.

Shoutout to Brayzac1 and EmuInABox for their unparalleled levels of sportsmanship.
--------------------------------

snippet.title: A New Base - The DarkOnion Chronicles(Episode 1)
snippet.description:
super rushed poorly put together pilot episode is DONE! WOO!!!!

Welcome to the DarkOnion Chronicles. The series takes place in a faction server devastated by war, as one small faction of mediocre players sets out to make a name for themselves. They go by the name... DarkOnion.

So yeah! It's a faction based machinima on The Archon (Cyan). We'll have episodes released every once and a while, and you too can join in on the fun- DarkOnion is an open faction, and you can just hop on the server and join whenever you feel like it. If it's not full anyways... eh.... We'll occasionally need viewer help for scripts... and to take over, of course. (Also, just as a notice, if your power is really low (negative) from dying, there is a small chance I will kick you from the faction to increase our overall power- since its an open faction all this means is that when you re log on you have to rejoin the fac. Just.... those ppl that log off with -10/10... ;-; 

/f join DarkOnion (you have to actually be in Factions Cyan)

snippet.title: "Mega Walls" -  Parody of "Jingle Bells" (swearing)
snippet.description:
a compelling story of romance, adventure, and tragedy. 

released right after Christmas season because i dont care
(but mostly because I completely forgot about it until seeing a different music parody) 

unfortunately me crying sounds a lot like me barely being able to contain my laughter because when I think about it the two are rarely separate for me 

slightly less mediocre lyrics written by: technoblade. Shocking, I know. 

Ten minutes have gone by
And the walls are falling now
To the surface we go
Laughing while we play
Rush for the diamonds
Keep iron in the chest
But don't forget to have some fun
and always try your best!

Mega Walls, Mega Walls!
Rush out and join the fight!
Get some kills, and get some food
And die to an Enderman
Oh!
Mega Walls, Mega Walls
Your wither's getting wrecked,
It's already at five hundred
yet the game's barely began

When you joined this game,
It seemed fun at first glance
now you're trapped in spawn
and your team hasn't a chance!
They're clad in diamond gear
And you keep getting killed
It's becoming a lot more clear
It's probably some guild

Oh! 
Mega Walls, Mega Walls,
not looking so good now
Your wither is about to die
to some god damn max dread
yay!
Mega Walls, Mega Walls,
rush to your secret chest
where you find to your dismay
someone's stolen all your bread

Now you're completely done
So you try and run away
Up the tower you climb
Crying all the way
You're completely screwed
Hoping you can clutch
Sadly you don't have any food 
and teammates? not so much

Oh!
Mega Walls, Mega Walls
Where did we go wrong?
Enemies are closing in
and now you have died!
Oh!
Mega Walls, Mega Walls
Your entire team is dead.
That entire game was meaningless
Well, at least you tried

snippet.description:
through a series of mishaps caused by bad luck and poor decision making, the framer must forge his way to victory without his teammates by using only his cunning

basically no music due to a bug in recording rip 
--------------------------------
What the hell is Town of Salem?

Town of Salem is a heavily intellect based mind-game where 15 completely anonymous players are thrown into a town together under their own chosen aliases and given random roles. They must use their role's power and their gut instinct to figure out who's who, and ultimately win the game.

It's loads of fun! But takes a while to grasp. The basics: There are 3 members in the mafia, and 1 serial killer. The mafia and the serial killer both kill someone each night until they are eliminated themselves. The mafia know who their fellow mafia are, but the other 12 players in the game have no info about anyone. The townspeople must use their roles to figure out who is evil, and who is trustworthy. Further complicating things is the two neutral roles, who's goal is to manipulate the town into getting someone- often themselves- hung.

It's complicated as hell, ok? You'll get it in a few games, no worries. If you want to play yourself, here's a link:
http://www.blankmediagames.com/TownOfSalem/

and a link to the wikipedia to learn more:
http://town-of-salem.wikia.com/wiki/Town_of_Salem_Wiki:Main_Page

For this one, I decided that I would up the bar; bringing the average wins of the players in the clips up by at least 1000, to an astounding 2623 wins on average per person involved. Anyone can montage a random player... so I set out to make a montage of the extreme veterans of blitz. 

Fun fact: I started recording with sound a couple days ago, so every clip with sound was acquired within roughly 2 days. I was playing a lot, ok? :P I technically had sound for the other clips, but it wasn't usable because I had other music (or the same music at different timing) playing in the background. 

Please don't smack talk any players in this video... I don't want unnecessary enemies. This isn't meant to make them feel bad, it's to provide entertainment for you guys and to increase my overall PVP reputation (which is great advertisement ;3). Blitz is brutally unfair at times, which is very similar to Life.

snippet.title: #Professional - A Hunger Games Youtube Event Attempt
snippet.description:
One month ago, I made my own map, Norwegia. I thought... why not make a youtuber event? It'll be fun! Unfortunately, I confided in Hotrod for the hosting...

We started 45 minutes late with barely over half the players we needed, and brought in a few ringers such as Tesla.

Making matters worse, my family returned two hours early. Not only did they break their 'stay out of the room' request, they also brought another family over (including their 5 year old daughter) who promptly began playing with my sisters... 10 feet away

It was... #professional

all these dudes' channels:
http://www.youtube.com/user/NikoPlaysinHD - Niko
https://www.youtube.com/user/SupahCraft - BlackKeys
